  <item>
   <title>Announcing scribble-rainbow-delimiters</title>
   <link>https://yanyingwang.github.io/2021/05/announcing-scribble-rainbow-delimiters.html?utm_source=racket&amp;utm_medium=RSS</link>
   <guid isPermaLink="false">urn:https-yanyingwang-github-io:-2021-05-announcing-scribble-rainbow-delimiters-html</guid>
   <pubDate>Mon, 31 May 2021 22:00:49 UT</pubDate>
   <author>Yanying Wang</author>
   <description>
&lt;p&gt;Recently I extract my code from a former project &lt;a href="https://github.com/yanyingwang/rainbow-delimiters"&gt;rainbow-delimiters&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href="https://github.com/yanyingwang/scribble-rainbow-delimiters"&gt;scribble-rainbow-delimiters&lt;/a&gt;, which is useful for reading code on HTML page generated by &lt;a href="https://docs.racket-lang.org/scribble/index.html"&gt;Racket&amp;rsquo;s Scribble&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;a href="https://yanyingwang.github.io/2021/05/announcing-scribble-rainbow-delimiters.html?utm_source=racket&amp;amp;utm_medium=RSS"&gt;&lt;em&gt;More&amp;hellip;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description></item>
  <item>
   <title>Fathoming out Racket Package's version</title>
   <link>https://yanyingwang.github.io/2021/03/fathoming-out-racket-package-s-version.html?utm_source=racket&amp;utm_medium=RSS</link>
   <guid isPermaLink="false">urn:https-yanyingwang-github-io:-2021-03-fathoming-out-racket-package-s-version-html</guid>
   <pubDate>Mon, 29 Mar 2021 01:30:34 UT</pubDate>
   <author>Yanying Wang</author>
   <description>
&lt;p&gt;Recently I received an email of &lt;a href="https://github.com/yanyingwang/http-client/commit/d7450cd2842f3d6da07e8167d4b1e0f1fa2572a6#r48314895"&gt;a github comment&lt;/a&gt; on a Racket Package of mine named &lt;a href="https://github.com/yanyingwang/http-client/"&gt;http-client&lt;/a&gt;, which was announced to release by my post of &lt;a href="2020/09/announcing-the-release-of-http-client.html"&gt;Announcing the release of http-client&lt;/a&gt;. Until then, I realized there really exist someone using my packages except me. This also make me realize I already came to the point to fathom out the design of Racket&amp;rsquo;s package version that I tried before and abandoned because of being short on time, and I should commit to add versions to my packages.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;a href="https://yanyingwang.github.io/2021/03/fathoming-out-racket-package-s-version.html?utm_source=racket&amp;amp;utm_medium=RSS"&gt;&lt;em&gt;More&amp;hellip;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description></item>
